sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1891015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Poly-3-hydroxybutyrate, P(3HB), a kind of PHAs is synthesized by three enzymes. The A gene encodes for the 393 amino acids protein, 3-ketothiolase (PhaA). The B1 gene encodes for the 246 amino acids protein, acetoacetyl-CoA reductase (PhaB). The C1 gene encodes for the 589 amino acids protein, PHA Synthase (PhaC). These three enzymes can use Co-A as a substrate to produce P(3HB). IGEM team Tokyo Tech2012 designed and synthesized phaC1-A-B1gene sequence BBa_K934001, and expressed via constitutive promoter. In order to make the production process more controllable, we added heat-sensitive promoter(BBa_K873002) to the upstream of phaC1-A-B1 gene sequence （BBa_K934001）, constructing the heatshock inducible parts （BBa_1891015). Then we linked the newly synthesized part to the standard vector pSB1C3. The new plasmids can be used directly for heatshock induced expression in E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xinyu Liu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We get parts BBa_K934001 and BBa_K873002 from the kits sent by iGEM HQ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We used Spe I and Pst I to do dual digestion in PSB1C3 which contained HSP gene and recycled gene fragments in 2117bp, used Xbal I and Pst I to do dual digestion in PSB1C3 and recycled gene fragments in 4208bp.We use T4 ligase to link phaC1-A-B1 to the downstream of HSP promoter, then transform the vectors to Trans 5α for plasmid extraction.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K873002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a heat shock promoter, it refers to the transcription factor sigma32. when the temperature rise, the transcription factor sigma32 expresses a lot and binds to the RNA ploymerase to recognize the conserved sequence in -35 and -10 region, then the promoter starts to transcript.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: yue hu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We align the HSP promoters from the literature and then find the conserved sequence, then we just modified the promoter of groES of E.coli, and synthesis the part through BIC genescript.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The whole sequence of this part is only 90bp, so take a futher consideration if you intend to digest it for use.
